This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Du Maolin, southern weekend reporter

By Jiang Zhiyu, southern weekend staff writer

Editor in chief | Wu Xiaoyu

There was a tired voice on the other end of the line.

January 26,2020 afternoon, the second day of the Lunar New Year, until 5:00 pm, Guangdong Xuwen County Prevention and Control Work Leading Group Office of the advisory telephone finally dialed.

Since January 25, the county government has provided a hotel for Hubei residents to focus on medical observation, staff said, adding that there were too many people calling for more than a day. There were inquiries about hotel accommodation, there were inquiries about the number of days of isolation. As of 1500 hours on January 26, the 100-room hotel had received 81 Hubei tourists, according to the above-mentioned staff.

While most of their destinations are in Hainan, Xuwen County is the only place to cross the sea by car via Qiongzhou Strait.

In addition to hotels, the local government also provides free food and other services, by the government staff on duty, in case of an outbreak of disease, can be sent to the appropriate hospital.

This model is gradually adopted in many places.

On the evening of January 26, the Mayor of Wuhan, Zhou Xianwang, said at a news conference on the prevention and control of the new type of pneumonia that more than five million people had left the city because of the Spring Festival and the epidemic. According to big data on migration cited by the Institute of first-line cities of Finance and economics, between January 10 and January 22 during the Spring Festival travel period (before the city closure in Wuhan) , 60 percent to 70 percent of people from Wuhan left for other cities in Hubei Province, next are Henan Province, Hunan Province, Anhui Province, Chongqing City, Jiangxi Province.

Among them, some people left the Han Dynasty early festival can not go back, some people "closed the city" before running away. These "homeless" around Wuhan and even Hubei People, because of the sudden arrival of a serious epidemic, are experiencing some indescribable depression.

1
An identity you can't hide

1

###An identity you can't hide

On the afternoon of the 24th, the day of the New Year's Eve, a hubei-based hotel owner in Lingshui County received 12 hungry villagers.

Eight days ago, they crossed the sea via Qiongzhou Strait and arrived in Hainan for a two-month self-driving Spring Festival trip. The three families are looking forward to a warm Spring Festival holiday, and although news of the Wuhan epidemic has been reported from time to time along the way, everything is still going according to plan.

It was not until the early hours of January 23 that the city was declared closed. It was 52 days after the Lancet Medical Journal revealed the first case of pneumonia of unknown origin in Wuhan on December 1,2019.

The News of the "closure of the city" spread throughout the country. That morning, Lingshui County, a hotel to "have provisions" for the reason, declined a line of people to stay. The hotel informed him that he had received documents from the local police station, asking him to report to the police station and to go to the hospital to check and issue a certificate. In Chen Jiang to southern weekend reporter's narration, he consults Lingshui County Yingzhou Town police station, only needs to report to the local can.

Between the rising number of confirmed cases and the nervousness of the local population, most other hotels are reluctant to take on the risk of taking in Wuhan residents, even though there are now fixed-point reception units in many places.

Next thing I know, he's calling and calling and calling and calling. Hotels, bed and breakfasts, and even neighborhoods that I had stayed in before that day were all rejected. To hotels, restaurants, the waiter was laughing, a listen to is from Wuhan, the face immediately collapsed down.

In addition to direct rejection, there is also a disguised bid. Chen Jiang found a house for the three families, monthly rent more than 10,000, but the price tag on the tourism platform is 7000 yuan, "can live down already good. ".

However, the owner changed his mind again, on the grounds that the rest of the community did not approve of the Wuhan residents. "when the old ladies and grandfathers saw our car parked outside the community, they just took a picture of the license plate of our car and sent it to the group. They asked who it belonged to and didn't let him in. "

Travel became "vagrancy" .

A group of 12 people, the oldest 73, the youngest less than three years old. The old man became angry and the child in his arms cried and cried. At one point, he would let the old man and woman stay in the car, and wander the streets with friends in search of a meal.

In order to avoid getting into trouble, the owner hid the information that there were people from Wuhan staying in the hotel and provided three rooms on the top floor.

Finally have a foothold, Chen Jiang and take the initiative to the British town police station for the record. This brings the total number of confirmed cases of COVID-19 infection reported nationwide to 1,287.

EA license plate is conspicuous, Chen Jiang dare not stop in the hotel, but stopped in a street not far away, using paper to cover the license plate, but soon attracted traffic police, and had to stop.

As a result, late on New Year's Eve, a long car alarm blared through the warm night sky in Lingshui County, Hainan Province. Chen Jiang wakes with a start, the sound familiar again however, he realizes, the car was"smashed".

He got up quickly, ran to the balcony, overlooking. The night was dark, and he couldn't see what was happening, except for the roar of children's laughter and shouts of "This is the Wuhan bus. ".

Chen Jiang can only reply with wry smile, wait until coax laugh to disperse, just re-enter bedding. The next morning, I looked at the car, but the body was just hanging on the children's footprints, leaving some scratches, "no big deal. ".

"No big problem" , these days often hang in the mouth of Chen Jiang.

"If it weren't for the fact that you have been away from Wuhan for almost 14 days, I wouldn't dare take you in, " the hotel owner said, declining Chen's request to "take in" more of his fellow villagers.

More fellow-townsmen looking for a place to stay are people Chen Jiang knows from wechat groups set up by people in Hubei Province. In the group, people share news, cheer each other up, and talk about the "nowhere to go" crisis.

Sichuan and Chongqing tourism in the same girl art "people in the way. ". She and her mother arrived in Chongqing from Wuhan on Jan. 19, before the city announced a single case. On the 22nd, the mother and daughter arrived in Chengdu, the news came from the city, 25 night back to Wuhan flight was canceled. They're gonNA STAY AT THE B & B, and then the other one just cuts them off.

Xiaoyi has since hit the culture and tourism bureau, epidemic prevention stations, the mayor hotline. They were later informed that they could stay at the all season hotel, but when they arrived, the hotel was no longer available.

Southern weekend reporters called the all-season Hotel, the front desk staff said, because of the Wuhan People, by other guests complained about the hotel, the hotel will be closed tomorrow. "because there was no rule against people living in Wuhan, we had them check in anyway, and then they complained. "

According to the staff, the results of the temperature of the Wuhan guests are normal, but may be seen by other guests during the community inspection, "Wuhan People" identity can not be hidden. "The guests have their concerns and we are caught in the middle. "

Fortunately, a friend reached out. When he returned to his hometown, the House in Chengdu was vacated and the mother and daughter were given free lodging. Good care. Bought a oximeter and a thermometer. "secretly lend us to live. " Xiaoyi is very grateful.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xiaoyi shops for vegetables at a fresh produce supermarket near her temporary home in Chengdu, China, on January 27,2020

2
"there are more and more ugly words. "

2

###"there are more and more ugly words. "

In this epidemic prevention and control battle, first Wuhan people, then the entire province, to the last living in the land of everyone, are being pulled by an irresistible force. Even in their own homes, some people have suffered as never before because of their Hubei identity.

Wang's family has been in Chengdu for nearly a decade. On January 19, Wang's mother traveled to Chengdu from Xiaogan, Hubei Province, via Wuhan, to spend the New Year with her daughter. My mother was visiting Chengdu for the second time, and she soon felt the tension compared to the good impression she had made the previous time.

The turning point also happened in the early hours of January 23, when Wuhan was "sealed off" . It was only then that many people's perceptions of the epidemic suddenly became intense. A day later, the provincial government launched a level 1 emergency response to a public health emergency. On the evening of January 25, the provincial government's general office issued the first level response measures to respond to the COVID-19 infection.

The true and false about the epidemic hard to distinguish the news spread all over the streets and alleys, in Wang Xiao lived in the community, embarrassment also followed.

The owner group has revealed that Wang Xiao's mother just came from Hubei, the group immediately exploded in the pot. Wang, who understands the concerns of other residents, did not initially respond. The requirements of the community are clear: those with suspected symptoms are quarantined, while those without are quarantined at home for 14 days.

On January 26, Wang reported his situation to the community and the property. That afternoon, three Community Hospital doctors wearing protective clothing to the community, went to her home to ask about the situation, take temperature. After all the check-ins were completed, the doctors told them to quarantine themselves and leave.

It is this short of more than 20 minutes, the ambulance into the district news spread all over, finally spread to Wang Xiao home, became "a community residents were infected. ". Only the property manager in the owner group tried to explain, but the epidemic has not been reduced at the moment, no matter how many explanations appear to be weak.

"harsh words are coming more and more, " Wang said. To avoid unnecessary trouble, from the 26th onwards, the in-laws living in the same community did not gather together, to dinner, packed with lunch to her home.

That is, on this day, many copies of Wuhan returned home personnel personal information statistics table spread out.

After many Wuhan returnees cooperated with the investigation, personal information was leaked, including names, home addresses, telephone numbers, identity card numbers, return trips, and even college entrance examination results, the forms for recording the above information were circulated among various groups of villagers and small communities, and many people were harassed by strangers.

Wang Xiao can not help but feel sad and indignant. In her view, with the physical examination, truthfully fill in the personal information is beyond reproach, but where is the fine management of the relevant departments? "If I say I've been quarantined at home for 14 days, but who can prove it? When we get out of quarantine and move around the neighborhood, if someone else does get infected, I have 100 mouths. Who knows where he got infected? "

In response to these questions, a reporter from southern weekend called a community worker in Jinjiang District, Chengdu, on January 27. The other party said that the current supporting measures really have not kept up. "there are only so many people in the community, there are so many neighborhoods in charge, and the population base is so large, how can we take care of them? "

3
Government-designated accommodation

3

###Government-designated accommodation

In this accident and helpless "vagrancy" , some people even cold, some people to be lucky.

For days, it has been raining in Hangzhou. Hangzhou Xiaoshan International Airport have passed since the arrival of Flight TR188 from Singapore. On January 24, a flight from Singapore to Wuhan was cancelled due to the closure of the city, and 116 people from Wuhan were re-booked on the flight to Hangzhou.

After the plane landed, two passengers with fever were taken to the First People's Hospital in Xiaoshan District, the rest of the Wuhan passengers were quarantined at the airport hotel, and 219 other passengers were put under medical observation at the Party School of the Municipal Party Committee.

According to media reports, about 1 km away from the Party School also opened a reception area for family members, and become a door to connect the visitors and their families. Reports said the observation point was manned 24 hours a day, with robots delivering meals.

Further south, the city government of Xiamen, Fujian Province, removed all Wuhan tourists from the Gulangyu Island Island and placed the hotel under quarantine. Guangdong, Yunnan and Hainan have also issued announcements to help Hubei tourists travelling abroad.

On January 27, the Wuhan Municipal Bureau of Culture and tourism issued a letter to colleagues in the tourism industry in brother cities, which mentioned that 4,096 Wuhan tourists were still outside the country.

The letter specifically asks, "The cultural and tourism departments of the sister cities will continue to give great coordination and help to all Wuhan residents who are travelling outside, so that they can feel the warmth and care of the sister city more deeply. ".

Civilian power also plays a role. Some free up space for voluntary shelter, some sort of accommodation hotel address, someone to help contact the vehicle home. But before this, some people in the circle of friends left a "perhaps I will never come here again in this lifetime" , has set foot on the road back home.

Chen is particularly concerned about the efforts of local governments, and he has some doubts about whether the government can be more transparent about the information it publishes, such as how much the hotel charges, how to calculate the 14-day quarantine period and how hygienic the hotel is. He also worries that with so many people in Hubei staying together and quarantined in a hotel, if there are people with the latent period of the virus, others will become infected.

"The internet is full of 'go Wuhan, ' but when it comes to Wuhan people, it seems to be just a slogan, " Chen said.

In the original plan, Chen Jiang planned to return to Wuhan on the fourth day of the New Year, a journey of more than 1,700 kilometers that would normally take him one day and one night. The epidemic is still in doubt, and the journey home has never been so long and so far away.

At the request of the interviewees, Chen Jiang, Xiao Yi and Wang Xiao are pseudonyms
